{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880314391,"sessionID":"ses_2854b375cffeLE0cSfDuBS71a3","part":{"id":"prt_d7ab52bd6001DbQGxu3BdFbQS0","messageID":"msg_d7ab504ca001kF424HRziI0IRL","sessionID":"ses_2854b375cffeLE0cSfDuBS71a3","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_ba4348065c2d4b40b0296ecf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-035: client-go 类型客户端生成 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `client-go`\n- **Language:** Go\n- **Size:** L\n- **Base specs:** `deployment/client-go.md`\n\n## Scope\n\nThis delta spec covers the generated Kubernetes client-go library for API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`, module path `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`. It SHALL provide a typed Clientset, per-resource REST clients, SharedInformerFactory, Listers, and in-memory Fake clients for the `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` custom resources. All code SHALL be generated via `make gen-client` → `hack/update-codegen.sh` using `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1 with `--with-watch` flag.\n\n---\n\n## Clientset\n\n### Requirement: Interface contract\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `Clientset` implementing `Interface` with discovery and group accessor methods.\n\n#### Scenario: Interface exposes Discovery and RuntimeV1alpha1\n- **GIVEN** the `Interface` type is defined in `clientset/versioned/clientset.go`\n- **WHEN** the interface is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL declare `Discovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface` and `RuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface`\n\n#### Scenario: Clientset struct embeds DiscoveryClient\n- **GIVEN** the `Clientset` struct is defined\n- **WHEN** the struct fields are inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL embed `*discovery.DiscoveryClient` and hold `runtimeV1alpha1 *runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Client`\n\n### Requirement: Clientset constructors\n\nThe system SHALL provide four constructor functions for creating `Clientset` instances.\n\n#### Scenario: NewForConfig creates clientset from rest.Config\n- **GIVEN** a valid `*rest.Config` pointing to a Kubernetes API server\n- **WHEN** `NewForConfig(c)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `(*Clientset, nil)` with all group clients initialized, or `(*Clientset, error)` on failure\n\n#### Scenario: NewForConfigAndClient uses custom http.Client\n- **GIVEN** a valid `*rest.Config` and `*http.Client`\n- **WHEN** `NewForConfigAndClient(c, httpClient)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a `*Clientset` using the provided HTTP client for transport\n\n#### Scenario: NewForConfigOrDie panics on invalid config\n- **GIVEN** an invalid `*rest.Config` (e.g., malformed host)\n- **WHEN** `NewForConfigOrDie(c)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL panic\n\n#### Scenario: NewForConfigOrDie succeeds with valid config\n- **GIVEN** a valid `*rest.Config`\n- **WHEN** `NewForConfigOrDie(c)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a `*Clientset` without panicking\n\n#### Scenario: New creates clientset from rest.Interface\n- **GIVEN** a pre-configured `rest.Interface`\n- **WHEN** `New(restInterface)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a `*Clientset` with the typed client wired to the provided interface\n\n### Requirement: RuntimeV1alpha1 group accessor\n\nThe system SHALL provide access to the `runtime/v1alpha1` API group client.\n\n#### Scenario: RuntimeV1alpha1 returns typed group client\n- **GIVEN** a `Clientset` instance\n- **WHEN** `cs.RuntimeV1alpha1()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a `runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface`\n\n---\n\n## Typed Client — runtime/v1alpha1\n\n### Requirement: RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n\nThe system SHALL provide a group-level interface exposing REST client and resource getters.\n\n#### Scenario: RuntimeV1alpha1Interface contract\n- **GIVEN** the `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` is defined in `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go`\n- **WHEN** the interface is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL declare `RESTClient() rest.Interface`, `AgentRuntimesGetter`, and `CodeInterpretersGetter`\n\n#### Scenario: RuntimeV1alpha1Client implements the interface\n- **GIVEN** the `RuntimeV1alpha1Client` struct\n- **WHEN** its methods are inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL implement all methods of `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface`\n\n#### Scenario: REST defaults are configured correctly\n- **GIVEN** a `RuntimeV1alpha1Client` instance\n- **WHEN** its REST client is inspected\n- **THEN** `GroupVersion` SHALL be `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion`, `APIPath` SHALL be `/apis`, and negotiated serializer SHALL come from `clientset/versioned/scheme`\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntime typed client\n\nThe system SHALL provide a typed REST client for the `agentruntimes` resource.\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimesGetter interface\n- **GIVEN** the `AgentRuntimesGetter` interface\n- **WHEN** it is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL declare `AgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeInterface`\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeInterface CRUD — Create\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface` and a valid `*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime`\n- **WHEN** `Create(ctx, agentRuntime, opts)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL POST to `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes` and return the created object\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeInterface CRUD — Update\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface` and an existing `*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime`\n- **WHEN** `Update(ctx, agentRuntime, opts)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL PUT to the resource URL and return the updated object\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeInterface CRUD — UpdateStatus\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface` and an `*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime` with modified status\n- **WHEN** `UpdateStatus(ctx, agentRuntime, opts)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL PUT to the `/status` subresource endpoint\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeInterface CRUD — Get\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface` and a resource name\n- **WHEN** `Get(ctx, name, opts)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL GET the resource and return `*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime`\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeInterface CRUD — List\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface`\n- **WHEN** `List(ctx, opts)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL GET the collection and return `*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList`\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeInterface CRUD — Delete\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface` and a resource name\n- **WHEN** `Delete(ctx, name, opts)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL DELETE the resource and return `nil` on success or `error` on failure\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeInterface CRUD — DeleteCollection\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface`\n- **WHEN** `DeleteCollection(ctx, deleteOpts, listOpts)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL DELETE all resources matching `listOpts`\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeInterface CRUD — Watch\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface`\n- **WHEN** `Watch(ctx, opts)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL establish a watch stream and return `watch.Interface`\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeInterface CRUD — Patch\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface`, name, patch type, and patch data\n- **WHEN** `Patch(ctx, name, pt, data, opts, subresources...)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL PATCH the resource and return the patched `*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime`\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime resource plural\n- **GIVEN** the AgentRuntime REST client\n- **WHEN** the resource path is constructed\n- **THEN** the plural form SHALL be `agentruntimes`\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreter typed client\n\nThe system SHALL provide a typed REST client for the `codeinterpreters` resource with the same method shape as AgentRuntime.\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpretersGetter interface\n- **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpretersGetter` interface\n- **WHEN** it is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL declare `CodeInterpreters(namespace string) CodeInterpreterInterface`\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreterInterface methods\n- **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreterInterface`\n- **WHEN** its methods are inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL declare `Create`, `Update`, `UpdateStatus`, `Delete`, `DeleteCollection`, `Get`, `List`, `Watch`, `Patch` with types `*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter` / `CodeInterpreterList`\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter resource plural\n- **GIVEN** the CodeInterpreter REST client\n- **WHEN** the resource path is constructed\n- **THEN** the plural form SHALL be `codeinterpreters`\n\n### Requirement: Expansion hooks\n\nThe system SHALL provide empty expansion interfaces for custom method injection.\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeExpansion interface\n- **GIVEN** `generated_expansion.go`\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeExpansion` is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL be an empty interface `interface{}`\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreterExpansion interface\n- **GIVEN** `generated_expansion.go`\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterExpansion` is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL be an empty interface `interface{}`\n\n---\n\n## Scheme\n\n### Requirement: Scheme registration\n\nThe system SHALL register all `runtime/v1alpha1` types with a shared `Scheme`, `Codecs`, and `ParameterCodec`.\n\n#### Scenario: register.go builds Scheme\n- **GIVEN** `clientset/versioned/scheme/register.go`\n- **WHEN** the package is loaded\n- **THEN** `Scheme`, `Codecs`, and `ParameterCodec` SHALL be initialized as package-level variables\n\n#### Scenario: AddToScheme registers v1alpha1 types\n- **GIVEN** `AddToScheme` is called on a `*runtime.Scheme`\n- **WHEN** registration completes\n- **THEN** all `runtime/v1alpha1` types (AgentRuntime, AgentRuntimeList, CodeInterpreter, CodeInterpreterList) SHALL be registered\n\n---\n\n## Informer Factory\n\n### Requirement: SharedInformerFactory interface\n\nThe system SHALL provide a shared informer factory for cache-based event distribution.\n\n#### Scenario: SharedInformerFactory contract\n- **GIVEN** the `SharedInformerFactory` interface in `informers/externalversions/factory.go`\n- **WHEN** the interface is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL embed `internalinterfaces.SharedInformerFactory` and declare `Start`, `Shutdown`, `WaitForCacheSync`, `ForResource`, `InformerFor`, and `Runtime()` methods\n\n#### Scenario: NewSharedInformerFactory constructor\n- **GIVEN** a `versioned.Interface` client and `defaultResync time.Duration`\n- **WHEN** `NewSharedInformerFactory(client, defaultResync)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a `SharedInformerFactory` with the provided resync interval\n\n#### Scenario: NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions\n- **GIVEN** a client, resync duration, and options (`WithCustomResyncConfig`, `WithTweakListOptions`, `WithNamespace`, `WithTransform`)\n- **WHEN** `NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions(client, defaultResync, options...)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a configured `SharedInformerFactory` applying all provided options\n\n### Requirement: Start/Shutdown/WaitForCacheSync lifecycle\n\nThe system SHALL manage informer lifecycle through start, shutdown, and cache sync operations.\n\n#### Scenario: Start begins informer goroutines\n- **GIVEN** a `SharedInformerFactory` with registered informers\n- **WHEN** `Start(stopCh)` is called\n- **THEN** all registered informers SHALL begin watching their resources until `stopCh` is closed\n\n#### Scenario: Shutdown stops all informers\n- **GIVEN** a running `SharedInformerFactory`\n- **WHEN** `Shutdown()` is called\n- **THEN** all informers SHALL be stopped and resources released\n\n#### Scenario: WaitForCacheSync blocks until caches are ready\n- **GIVEN** a `SharedInformerFactory` with started informers\n- **WHEN** `WaitForCacheSync(stopCh)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL block until all informers have synced their caches or `stopCh` is closed, returning a `map[reflect.Type]bool`\n\n### Requirement: Group and version accessors\n\nThe system SHALL provide hierarchical accessors for group → version → informer navigation.\n\n#### Scenario: Runtime() returns group interface\n- **GIVEN** a `SharedInformerFactory`\n- **WHEN** `factory.Runtime()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `externalversionsruntime.Interface`\n\n#### Scenario: V1alpha1() returns version interface\n- **GIVEN** a group `Interface`\n- **WHEN** `group.V1alpha1()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `v1alpha1.Interface` with `AgentRuntimes()` and `CodeInterpreters()` accessors\n\n### Requirement: Per-type informers\n\nThe system SHALL provide informer and lister access for each resource type.\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeInformer interface\n- **GIVEN** the `AgentRuntimeInformer` interface\n- **WHEN** it is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL declare `Informer() cache.SharedIndexInformer` and `Lister() runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeLister`\n\n#### Scenario: NewAgentRuntimeInformer constructor\n- **GIVEN** a `versioned.Interface` client and `resync time.Duration`\n- **WHEN** `NewAgentRuntimeInformer(client, namespace, resync, indexers)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a `cache.SharedIndexInformer` watching AgentRuntime resources\n\n#### Scenario: NewFilteredAgentRuntimeInformer\n- **GIVEN** a client, namespace, resync, indexers, and `tweakListOptions`\n- **WHEN** `NewFilteredAgentRuntimeInformer` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return an informer with list options modified by `tweakListOptions`\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreterInformer mirrors AgentRuntimeInformer\n- **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreterInformer` interface\n- **WHEN** it is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL declare the same methods as `AgentRuntimeInformer` but returning `CodeInterpreterLister`\n\n### Requirement: Generic resource routing\n\nThe system SHALL route GVR lookups to the correct typed informer.\n\n#### Scenario: ForResource routes agentruntimes\n- **GIVEN** `ForResource(v1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion.WithResource(\"agentruntimes\"))`\n- **WHEN** the method is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `f.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()` wrapped in a `GenericInformer`\n\n#### Scenario: ForResource routes codeinterpreters\n- **GIVEN** `ForResource(v1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion.WithResource(\"codeinterpreters\"))`\n- **WHEN** the method is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `f.Runtime().V1alpha1().CodeInterpreters().Informer()` wrapped in a `GenericInformer`\n\n#### Scenario: ForResource returns error for unknown resource\n- **GIVEN** `ForResource` with an unrecognized GVR\n- **WHEN** the method is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `(nil, error)`\n\n### Requirement: internalinterfaces\n\nThe system SHALL define base factory interfaces for informer construction.\n\n#### Scenario: NewInformerFunc signature\n- **GIVEN** the `internalinterfaces` package\n- **WHEN** `NewInformerFunc` is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL be `func(versioned.Interface, time.Duration) cache.SharedIndexInformer`\n\n#### Scenario: internalinterfaces.SharedInformerFactory\n- **GIVEN** the `internalinterfaces.SharedInformerFactory` interface\n- **WHEN** it is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL declare `Start(stopCh <-chan struct{})` and `InformerFor(obj runtime.Object, newFunc NewInformerFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer`\n\n#### Scenario: TweakListOptionsFunc\n- **GIVEN** the `TweakListOptionsFunc` type\n- **WHEN** it is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL be `func(*metav1.ListOptions)`\n\n---\n\n## Listers\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntimeLister\n\nThe system SHALL provide a read-only caching layer for AgentRuntime objects.\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeLister interface\n- **GIVEN** the `AgentRuntimeLister` interface in `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`\n- **WHEN** it is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL declare `List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)`, `AgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister`, and `AgentRuntimeListerExpansion`\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister interface\n- **GIVEN** the `AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister` interface\n- **WHEN** it is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL declare `List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)`, `Get(name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)`, and `AgentRuntimeNamespaceListerExpansion`\n\n#### Scenario: NewAgentRuntimeLister uses correct GroupResource\n- **GIVEN** `NewAgentRuntimeLister(indexer cache.Indexer)` is called\n- **WHEN** the lister is created\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `runtimev1alpha1.Resource(\"agentruntime\").GroupResource()` for error reporting\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterLister\n\nThe system SHALL provide a read-only caching layer for CodeInterpreter objects with the same pattern.\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreterLister interface\n- **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreterLister` interface\n- **WHEN** it is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL declare `List`, `CodeInterpreters(namespace) CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister`, and `CodeInterpreterListerExpansion`\n\n#### Scenario: NewCodeInterpreterLister uses correct GroupResource\n- **GIVEN** `NewCodeInterpreterLister(indexer)` is called\n- **WHEN** the lister is created\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `Resource(\"codeinterpreter\").GroupResource()`\n\n### Requirement: Lister expansion interfaces\n\nThe system SHALL provide empty expansion interfaces for all lister types.\n\n#### Scenario: All four expansion interfaces are empty\n- **GIVEN** `expansion_generated.go`\n- **WHEN** the file is inspected\n- **THEN** `AgentRuntimeListerExpansion`, `AgentRuntimeNamespaceListerExpansion`, `CodeInterpreterListerExpansion`, and `CodeInterpreterNamespaceListerExpansion` SHALL all be empty interfaces\n\n---\n\n## Fake Clients\n\n### Requirement: Fake typed clients\n\nThe system SHALL provide in-memory fake implementations of typed interfaces for testing.\n\n#### Scenario: Fake runtime group client\n- **GIVEN** `fake/fake_runtime_client.go`\n- **WHEN** the `FakeRuntimeV1alpha1` struct is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL implement `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` and embed `*testing.Fake`\n\n#### Scenario: Fake AgentRuntime client\n- **GIVEN** `fake/fake_agentruntime.go`\n- **WHEN** the fake AgentRuntime client is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL implement `AgentRuntimeInterface` using `*testing.Fake` actions\n\n#### Scenario: Fake CodeInterpreter client\n- **GIVEN** `fake/fake_codeinterpreter.go`\n- **WHEN** the fake CodeInterpreter client is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL implement `CodeInterpreterInterface` using `*testing.Fake` actions\n\n### Requirement: Fake clientset\n\nThe system SHALL provide a fake `Clientset` for integration testing without a real API server.\n\n#### Scenario: NewSimpleClientset creates fake clientset with objects\n- **GIVEN** `fake.NewSimpleClientset(objects...)` is called with initial runtime objects\n- **WHEN** the fake clientset is returned\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain the provided objects in its tracker and implement `versioned.Interface`\n\n#### Scenario: NewClientset creates fake clientset with custom reactor\n- **GIVEN** `fake.NewClientset(client, objects...)` is called\n- **WHEN** the fake clientset is returned\n- **THEN** it SHALL use the provided `*restclient.RESTClient` and tracker\n\n#### Scenario: Fake clientset Scheme registration\n- **GIVEN** `fake/register.go`\n- **WHEN** the package is loaded\n- **THEN** it SHALL wire the same scheme as the real clientset for type recognition\n\n---\n\n## Regeneration\n\n### Requirement: make gen-client target\n\nThe system SHALL provide a Makefile target to regenerate all client-go code.\n\n#### Scenario: make gen-client runs update-codegen.sh\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile defines `gen-client`\n- **WHEN** `make gen-client` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL invoke `hack/update-codegen.sh`\n\n#### Scenario: update-codegen.sh uses correct code-generator version\n- **GIVEN** `hack/update-codegen.sh`\n- **WHEN** the script is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1\n\n#### Scenario: code-generator flags include --with-watch\n- **GIVEN** the code-generator invocation in `update-codegen.sh`\n- **WHEN** the command is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL include `--with-watch` flag for watch support\n\n#### Scenario: output package is correct\n- **GIVEN** the code-generator invocation\n- **WHEN** the output package flag is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL be `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`\n\n---\n\n## File Index\n\n### Requirement: All generated files exist at expected paths\n\nThe system SHALL produce the following file structure under `client-go/`.\n\n#### Scenario: Clientset files\n- **GIVEN** code generation completes\n- **THEN** the following files SHALL exist:\n  - `clientset/versioned/clientset.go`\n  - `clientset/versioned/scheme/register.go`\n  - `clientset/versioned/scheme/doc.go`\n  - `clientset/versioned/fake/clientset_generated.go`\n  - `clientset/versioned/fake/register.go`\n  - `clientset/versioned/fake/doc.go`\n\n#### Scenario: Typed client files\n- **GIVEN** code generation completes\n- **THEN** the following files SHALL exist:\n  - `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go`\n  - `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`\n  - `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go`\n  - `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/generated_expansion.go`\n  - `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go`\n  - `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_runtime_client.go`\n  - `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_agentruntime.go`\n  - `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_codeinterpreter.go`\n  - `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/doc.go`\n\n#### Scenario: Informer files\n- **GIVEN** code generation completes\n- **THEN** the following files SHALL exist:\n  - `informers/externalversions/factory.go`\n  - `informers/externalversions/generic.go`\n  - `informers/externalversions/runtime/interface.go`\n  - `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go`\n  - `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`\n  - `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go`\n  - `informers/externalversions/internalinterfaces/factory_interfaces.go`\n\n#### Scenario: Lister files\n- **GIVEN** code generation completes\n- **THEN** the following files SHALL exist:\n  - `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`\n  - `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go`\n  - `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/expansion_generated.go`\n\n---\n\n## File Changes\n\n| Action | File | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/clientset.go` | `Clientset`, `Interface`, constructors |\n| Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/scheme/register.go` | Scheme / codecs for generated client |\n| Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/scheme/doc.go` | Doc |\n| Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/fake/clientset_generated.go` | Fake clientset implementation |\n| Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/fake/register.go` | Fake scheme wiring |\n| Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n| Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go` | `RuntimeV1alpha1Client`, `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` |\n| Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeInterface`, typed REST client |\n| Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterInterface`, typed REST client |\n| Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/generated_expansion.go` | Expansion interfaces |\n| Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Doc |\n| Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_runtime_client.go` | Fake runtime group client |\n| Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_agentruntime.go` | Fake AgentRuntime client |\n| Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_codeinterpreter.go` | Fake CodeInterpreter client |\n| Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n| Create | `client-go/informers/externalversions/factory.go` | `SharedInformerFactory`, options, lifecycle |\n| Create | `client